         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (if one recognises [that]) through wisdom /// /// [SKT] (then) he turns away (from sorrow)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>332</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] (this is the way) to (complete purity) [SKT] (I have) taught (you the way) /// /// [TB] I have taught you the way</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] ([this] is) to be done (by you;) /// /// [TB] ([this] is) to be done (by you;) [SKT] (Tathāgatas) teach [it]</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] it destroys the thorn of craving</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] it is straight, and it is ([the way of] exertion)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] like (the only certain) way (of flamingos to the pond) /// /// [SKT] (which) Śākyamuni attained concentrated</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] and (which) he teaches (constantly) in the assemblies /// /// [TB] (and which he teaches) constantly in the assemblies [SKT] (seeing the end of rebirth and old age) [he proclaims] the only certain [way]</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] seeing (the end of rebirth and old age [he proclaims] the only certain [way]) [SKT] (he proclaims) the [only certain] way, (kind and compassionate) /// /// [TB] he proclaims the [only certain] way, (kind and compassionate)</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><bibl><title corresp="ref:bernhard1965"/><citedRange>194-196</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:chakravarti1930"/><citedRange>143-146</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:hahn2007"/><citedRange>47-48</citedRange></bibl></note><note type="philcomment">The size of the lacuna between the left hand fragment <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-ioltoch772"/> and the right hand fragment IOL Toch 122 may be estimated between 7 and 14 akṣaras on the basis of the following speculative restorations (for several correspondences there are more possibilities, which are not noted here):</note><note type="philcomment">The difference between 7 akṣ. for lines a3/b3 and 10-14 akṣ. for lines a1-2/b4-5 suggests that a3/b3 contained the string hole space. On the basis of IOL Toch 122 b2, which preserves 7 full akṣaras on 6,4 cms, the size of a lacuna of 11-12 akṣaras may have been approximately 10 cms.</note><note type="remarks">This fragment (IOL Toch 122, right) is from the same leaf as <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-ioltoch772"/>, left: IOL Toch 772 a1-3 and IOL Toch 772 b3-5 precede IOL Toch 122 a1-3 and IOL Toch 122 b3-5 by approximately 7 to 14 akṣ. or 10 cms (see the philological commentary for details). Traces of lines a5 and b1, which contained Uv.12.10c-11d, can be discerned. If the string hole space covered only a3/b3, the manuscript must originally have had 5 lines.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment">Uv.12.8b-c <hi>prajñayā paśyate yadā | atha nirvidyate duḥkhād</hi></note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment"><hi>(pra)jñayā (paśyate yadā aiśamñesa lkāṣṣäṃ kr<hi rend="subscript">u</hi>i atha) nirvidyate</hi> = 14 akṣ.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">Uv.12.8d-9a <hi>eṣa mārgo viśuddhaye // 8 ākhyāto vo mayā mārgaḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment"><hi>ā(khyāto vo mayā mārgaḥ ākṣu)sa</hi> = 10 akṣ.</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment">Uv.12.9c-d <hi>yuṣmābhir eva karaṇīyam ākhyātāras tathāgatāḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment"><hi>(ka)ra(ṇīyam yessa yama)ṣṣälle</hi> = 7 akṣ.</note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment">Uv.12.10b <hi>tṛṣṇāśalyanikṛntanaḥ</hi>; all manuscripts used by <bibl><title corresp="ref:bernhard1965"/><citedRange>195</citedRange></bibl>, including this one, read <hi>°nikṛndana°</hi></note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment">Uv.12.12a <hi>eṣo ’ñjaso hy eṣa ca vai parākramas</hi></note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment">Uv.12.12b-c <hi>tv ekāyano haṃsapatho yathā hrade | yam adhyagāc chākyamuniḥ samāhitas</hi></note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment"><hi>mäkt(e yolmeścä • yam adhya)gāc</hi> = 7 akṣ.</note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment">Uv.12.12d-13a <hi>tam eva cākhyāti gaṇeṣv abhīkṣṇaśaḥ || 12 ekāyanaṃ jātijarāntadarśī</hi></note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment"><hi>gaṇ(eṣv abhīkṣṇaśaḥ tā<hi rend="subscript">u</hi> ṣpä aksaṣṣäṃ kraupe)nne</hi> = 12 akṣ.</note><note corresp="#b5" type="philcomment">Uv.12.13a-b <hi>ekāyanaṃ jātijarāntadarśī mārgaṃ vadaty eṣa hitānukampī</hi></note><note corresp="#b5" type="philcomment"><hi>mā(rgaṃ vadaty eṣa hitānukampī ytā)ri</hi> = 11 akṣ.</note></p>
         </div>
