               <item n="m_philcomment_old">&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a1.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.12.8b-c &lt;i&gt;prajñayā paśyate yadā | atha nirvidyate duḥkhād&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a2.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.12.8d-9a &lt;i&gt;eṣa mārgo viśuddhaye // 8 ākhyāto vo mayā mārgaḥ&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a3.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.12.9c-d &lt;i&gt;yuṣmābhir eva karaṇīyam ākhyātāras tathāgatāḥ&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a4.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.12.10b &lt;i&gt;tṛṣṇāśalyanikṛntanaḥ&lt;/i&gt;; all manuscripts used by [[Bernhard 1965]]: 195, including this one, read &lt;i&gt;°nikṛndana°&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b2.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.12.12a &lt;i&gt;eṣo ’ñjaso hy eṣa ca vai parākramas&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b3.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.12.12b-c &lt;i&gt;tv ekāyano haṃsapatho yathā hrade | yam adhyagāc chākyamuniḥ samāhitas&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b4.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.12.12d-13a &lt;i&gt;tam eva cākhyāti gaṇeṣv abhīkṣṇaśaḥ || 12 ekāyanaṃ jātijarāntadarśī&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b5.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.12.13a-b &lt;i&gt;ekāyanaṃ jātijarāntadarśī mārgaṃ vadaty eṣa hitānukampī&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The size of the lacuna between the left hand fragment [[IOL Toch 772]] and the right hand fragment IOL Toch 122 may be estimated between 7 and 14 akṣaras on the basis of the following speculative restorations (for several correspondences there are more possibilities, which are not noted here):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a1.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;(pra)jñayā (paśyate yadā aiśamñesa lkāṣṣäṃ kr&lt;sub&gt;u&lt;/sub&gt;i atha) nirvidyate&lt;/i&gt; = 14 akṣ.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a2.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;ā(khyāto vo mayā mārgaḥ ākṣu)sa&lt;/i&gt; = 10 akṣ.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a3.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;(ka)ra(ṇīyam yessa yama)ṣṣälle&lt;/i&gt; = 7 akṣ.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b3.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;mäkt(e yolmeścä • yam adhya)gāc&lt;/i&gt; = 7 akṣ.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b4.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;gaṇ(eṣv abhīkṣṇaśaḥ tā&lt;sub&gt;u&lt;/sub&gt; ṣpä aksaṣṣäṃ kraupe)nne&lt;/i&gt; = 12 akṣ.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b5.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;mā(rgaṃ vadaty eṣa hitānukampī ytā)ri&lt;/i&gt; = 11 akṣ.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The difference between 7 akṣ. for lines a3/b3 and 10-14 akṣ. for lines a1-2/b4-5 suggests that a3/b3 contained the string hole space. On the basis of IOL Toch 122 b2, which preserves 7 full akṣaras on 6,4 cms, the size of a lacuna of 11-12 akṣaras may have been approximately 10 cms.&lt;/p&gt;</item>
